description: This describes how to call a conversion webhook

clientConfig.description: The instructions for calling the webhook if strategy is `"Webhook"`. This cannot be set if the conversion strategy is not `"Webhook"`.

conversionReviewVersions.description: An ordered list of preferred `ConversionReview` versions the Webhook expects. The API server will use the first version in the list which it supports. If none of the versions specified in this list are supported by API server, conversion will fail for the custom resource. If a persisted webhook configuration specifies allowed versions and does not include any versions known to the API Server, calls to the webhook will fail. The acceptable versions are [`"v1"`, `"v1beta1"`].
